---
title: Breakfast Chorizo Egg Polenta Pancakes with Spinach and Spicy Tomato Sauce
description: Polenta is probably something you’d expect to eat at a sophisticated Italian restaurant. But for breakfast? Trust us, it works. Making it into cakes with a delightfully crispy outside is surprisingly uncomplicated: if you can cook in a pan, you can cook these. Their creaminess is the perfect counterpart to smoky chorizo, a gently spiced tomato sauce, and savory spinach.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w17-r12-breakfast-717d8a10.jpg
